[{"content":"Kessel Knowledge Base — Sample Document\n\nProject Overview\nKessel is an internal knowledge base system that allows teams to query private documentation using natural language. It uses a retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) architecture: documents are chunked, embedded, and stored in a vector database. At query time, the most relevant chunks are retrieved and passed as context to a large language model, which synthesises a grounded answer.\n\nKey Principles\n- Answers are always grounded in indexed content. Kessel will not speculate or hallucinate beyond what the documents say.\n- Source documents are never exposed to end users — only synthesised answers are returned.\n- The system is designed to be self-hosted so that sensitive documents never leave your infrastructure.\n\nGetting Started\nTo add knowledge to Kessel, place .txt or .md files in the docs/ directory and run the ingest script. Once ingestion is complete, start the server and send questions to the POST /ask endpoint.","embedding":[-0.015108607,-0.060023371,-0.003109188,-0.072885573,0.006554097,-0.024421636,-0.001618227,-0.029506547,0.014364406,0.026363712,-0.029598724,0.041307472,-0.002895116,-0.02331177,-0.023363154,-0.02201226,0.014414843,0.063328654,0.041740254,0.015550084,-0.007928708,0.040101178,-0.010653228,0.020529656,-0.059782438,-0.012771899,0.046682592,-0.037336808,0.006010137,-0.077462077,0.018276615,0.039581243,0.007511646,0.018554421,0.012175404,0.048666514,0.017924633,-0.065284751,-0.033008289,-0.015342274,-0.01869625,-0.032317229,-0.062520169,0.01167114,0.036143076,-0.005234603,-0.022079378,-0.011299144,0.039917003,0.003071082,-0.013385026,-0.03655095,-0.000788686,0.044251908,0.002753701,0.038907327,-0.049538363,-0.01313634,0.077936642,0.006089457,0.012955943,0.005040593,0.014785575,0.022307277,0.054171756,0.029023334,0.009151854,0.00198887,-0.026434332,-0.036484394,-0.020383459,-0.040337957,-0.036858596,-0.022359384,0.044537295,-0.016467692,-0.01387422,0.031139309,-0.044919